On Tue, 18 Feb 2003, 1970Westy bus wrote:

> SO you have disc brakes that are different then the brakes of
> your 78.

Not different in stopping ability, only in pad thickness.

> My point is that the type 1 engine will be dealing with the vacuum for them.
> Make sure its connected.

Good point.  The vacuum connection is a large nipple just below the
carburator flange on the one-year-only '71 manifold.  Often another engine
gets transplanted in with bodged vacuum connections to the smaller ports.

George Lyle
